多謝你帶我們來看演唱會 Ted 再見!
Thank you for taking us to the concert,though,ted. Yeah. Bye!

27
00:03:32,410 --> 00:03:36,380
再見 我叫Ed 不是Ted
Byebye. It's ed,not ted.

28
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:25,870
最近一名受害者叫Tara Farris 20歲
The latest victim is tara farris,20.

29
00:04:25,900 --> 00:04:27,620
她是兩周內的第3名受害者
She's the third victim in 2 weeks.

30
00:04:27,650 --> 00:04:30,180
都是上下班的人在公路出口發現的
All found on freeway offramps by commuters.

31
00:04:30,190 --> 00:04:31,510
他沒有把屍體藏起來
Well,he's not hiding them.

32
00:04:31,530 --> 00:04:34,970
扔在洛杉磯早高峰的公路上 他想讓人們發現屍體
An l.a.freeway during morning rush hour? He wants them found.

33
00:04:34,980 --> 00:04:36,300
越快發現越好
Quickly.

34
00:04:36,320 --> 00:04:39,570
她們還穿著衣服 基本不會嚇到路人
Well,they're still dressed. That minimizes the shock value.

35
00:04:39,580 --> 00:04:42,230
也許他關心她們 希望她們能得到照顧?
Maybe he's concerned for them. Think he wants them taken care of?

36
00:04:42,240 --> 00:04:45,020
受害者都沒遭受性侵犯
No signs of sexual assault on any of the victims.

37
00:04:45,030 --> 00:04:46,570
看她臉色多蒼白
Look how pale she is.

38
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:48,750
她們都有嚴重脫血
All of them were severely hypovolemic.

39
00:04:48,780 --> 00:04:51,160
Tara體內剩下不到1品脫的血
Tara had less than a pint of blood in her.

40
00:04:51,180 --> 00:04:53,460
看這個 前兩個受害者 都剩下3品脫多的血
Look at this. The first 2 had more than 3 pints each.

41
00:04:53,470 --> 00:04:57,150
如果他的目標是放血 不明嫌犯顯然已經駕輕就熟
If exsanguination is the goal, the unsub is definitely becoming more proficient.

42
00:04:57,160 --> 00:05:00,260
這一點是新的 Tara是唯一留下信息的受害者
This is new. Tara's the only victim to have a written message.

43
00:05:00,270 --> 00:05:01,270
"你這騙子"
"the liar."

44
00:05:01,280 --> 00:05:03,750
"你這"騙子 很怪對吧?
"the" liar. That's strange,isn't it?

45
00:05:03,760 --> 00:05:06,930
不是"一個騙子"或僅僅"騙子"
Not a liar or just liar.

46
00:05:07,260 --> 00:05:09,070
你到底撒什麼謊了 Tara?
So what did you lie about,tara?

47
00:05:09,090 --> 00:05:12,580
所有受害者都被勒死 然後放血
All of the victims appear to have been strangled and then bled out

48
00:05:12,590 --> 00:05:14,530
喉嚨上有一樣的傷口
through identical wounds in the throat.

49
00:05:14,550 --> 00:05:18,470
等等 說真的 這印子是尖牙咬的嗎?
Wait…seriously, are those supposed to be fang marks?

50
00:05:18,480 --> 00:05:21,250
受害者身上所有傷口都留有唾液
All of the wounds on the victims were covered in saliva.

51
00:05:21,270 --> 00:05:24,710
人類唾液 好像是... 有人喝了她們的血
Human saliva, as though… Someone drank their blood.

52
00:05:34,300 --> 00:06:06,170
<font color=#FF7F00>犯罪心理 第五季 第7集</font>
<font color=#DB70DB>Criminal Minds Season05 Episode07 The Performer</font>

53
00:06:06,200 --> 00:06:09,620
在所有描述邪惡鬼怪的黑暗文字
In all the darkest pages of the malign supernatural,

54
00:06:09,640 --> 00:06:13,370
沒有比描述吸血鬼傳統更可怕的了
There is no more terrible tradition than that of the vampire.

55
00:06:13,380 --> 00:06:15,900
他是魔界的賤民
A pariah even among demons.

56
00:06:15,910 --> 00:06:18,080
作家 Montague Summers
Writer montague summers.

57
00:06:18,090 --> 00:06:21,640
好的 謝謝 他們已經在洛杉磯 安排了特遣部隊
Ok,thanks. So they've already set up a task force in los angeles.

58
00:06:21,650 --> 00:06:23,640
這不是他們第一宗連環殺人案
This isn't their first serial case.

59
00:06:23,660 --> 00:06:26,250
還記得Owen Kim探員嗎? 上次查跟蹤案的
You remember detective owen kim? From the stalker case.

60
00:06:26,260 --> 00:06:28,980
你還記得那宗案子 對吧 Spence?
You remember that case, don't you,spence?

61
00:06:29,490 --> 00:06:31,140
我是記得那案子
I do remember that case.

62
00:06:31,150 --> 00:06:34,100
還有沒有... 跟那個Lila聯繫了?
Yeah,you ever talk to,um, lila anymore?

63
00:06:34,130 --> 00:06:35,750
我想我們現在應該 把注意力集中在這個案子上
You know,i think we should probably focus on this case right now.

64
00:06:35,780 --> 00:06:37,480
這樣做比較合適
It's a little more pertinent.

65
00:06:39,430 --> 00:06:41,450
好 說說吸血的傢伙吧 Reid
All right,so tell us about blooddrinkers,reid.

66
00:06:41,470 --> 00:06:45,310
嗜人血者 或者叫臨床吸人膏血者 被稱作Renfield綜合癥
Human blood consumption, or clinical vampirism, is known as renfield's syndrome,

67
00:06:45,340 --> 00:06:49,630
是根據布拉姆·斯托克的小說<德古拉>中 一個吃昆蟲的角色而命名的
Named after the insecteating character in bram stoker's novel "dracula."

68
00:06:49,650 --> 00:06:51,370
他們是虐待狂嗎? 不一定
Are they sadists? Not necessarily.

69
00:06:51,380 --> 00:06:55,140
給受害者帶來的傷害通常是順帶的 他們關注的是人血
Pain to the victim is usually only a byproduct. Blood is the focus.

70
00:06:55,150 --> 00:06:58,540
Renfield綜合癥通常伴有 不同程度的精神分裂癥
Renfield's syndrome is usually accompanied by varying levels of schizophrenia

71
00:06:58,570 --> 00:07:01,970
如果發展得更厲害 更會有典型的同類相食
And occasionally more classic cannibalism if the condition evolves.

72
00:07:01,990 --> 00:07:05,070
典型的同類相食 咱這工作真是開眼界呀
Classic cannibalism. Lovely job we have.

73
00:07:05,080 --> 00:07:08,340
這麼說吧…真實的案件極少
I will say this… true cases are exceedingly rare.

74
00:07:08,360 --> 00:07:10,580
總算讓人舒了口氣 算是吧
That's comforting. Sort of.

75
00:07:10,590 --> 00:07:13,350
Renfield癥患者可能罕見 吸血鬼卻到處都是
Renfield's may be rare, but vampires are anything but.

76
00:07:13,360 --> 00:07:17,020
洛杉磯有非常龐大的 "吸血不死"亞文化群
And there's a huge subculture in los angeles of the reddrinking undead.

77
00:07:17,050 --> 00:07:19,260
我怎麼見怪不怪呢
Why is that not a surprise?

78
00:07:20,790 --> 00:07:22,700
Garcia 這些人都吸血嗎?
Garcia,all these people drink blood?

79
00:07:22,720 --> 00:07:26,200
正相反 大部分只是像Prentiss高中時那樣 搞一身裝扮 然後裝神弄鬼
Au contraire. They mostly just dress up like prentiss did in high school and they make believe.

80
00:07:26,210 --> 00:07:28,460
品味各不相同呀 這兩個根本是天壤之別
It's all kinds of delicious. It's not the same thing at all.

81
00:07:28,470 --> 00:07:32,630
事實上 我們該說不明嫌犯是個 吸血鬼主義者 而不是吸血鬼
As a matter of fact, we should refer to this unsub as a vampirist,not a vampire.

82
00:07:32,660 --> 00:07:36,650
他們被亞文化吸引 僅僅是因為它對人血的崇拜
And they would be attracted to the subculture merely for its professed worship of blood.

83
00:07:36,660 --> 00:07:39,490
好吧 我繼續在各種網站挖掘
Ok,i'm going to continue spelunking through the various online sites,

84
00:07:39,510 --> 00:07:42,000
看有沒啥東西跳出來 咬我一口
See if anything jumps up and bites me.

85
00:07:42,010 --> 00:07:45,820
謝謝 寶貝... 謝謝 Penelope 跟緊點
Thanks,baby g… Thanks,penelope. Stay close.

86
00:07:46,500 --> 00:07:48,600
遵命 長官  Garcia斷線
Yes,sir. Garcia out.

87
00:07:48,610 --> 00:07:51,150
各位 還有一點 吸血鬼主義者貪得無厭
You guys,one more thing… vampirists are coveters.

88
00:07:51,170 --> 00:07:54,180
一般都是和受害者有某種聯繫
They most generally always have some sort of relationship with the victim,

89
00:07:54,210 --> 00:07:57,100
就算只是一面之緣 也會讓他們如癡如醉
Even if it's tangential. And they're likely to become obsessed.

90
00:07:57,110 --> 00:08:00,290
他們肯定在某方面有交集
They've almost certainly crossed paths in some way.

91
00:08:03,550 --> 00:08:06,370
<i>加利福尼亞州 洛杉磯</i>

92
00:08:38,440 --> 00:08:42,060
沒事的 只有我 是Ray 你咋還在睡呢?
It's ok. It's just me. It's ray. You still in bed?

93
00:08:42,070 --> 00:08:43,400
我病了
I'm sick.

94
00:08:43,430 --> 00:08:45,940
聽著 Dante 你已經遲到了
Look,dante, you're already late.

95
00:08:45,950 --> 00:08:49,280
別這麼叫我 對不起 夥計 你得出發了 好嗎?
Don't call me that. Sorry,but,man, you gotta get going,ok?

96
00:08:50,140 --> 00:08:51,760
我說不去
I said no.

97
00:08:51,770 --> 00:08:54,420
唱片公司又要發火了 如果你不…
The record company is gonna be pissed again.If you're not…

98
00:08:54,430 --> 00:08:56,210
出去!
get out!

99
00:08:56,220 --> 00:08:59,830
我知道你討厭這些聚會 但是你要把唱片賣出去呀
I know you hate these parties, but you've got to sell the record.

100
00:08:59,850 --> 00:09:02,890
你不能撒手不管 這是你的工作 夥計
You can't blow this off. It's your job,man.

101
00:09:02,900 --> 00:09:06,270
我的工作則是催你
And it's my job to make you go.

102
00:09:08,110 --> 00:09:09,880
必須變成他嗎?
Do I have to be him?

103
00:09:09,910 --> 00:09:11,790
你知道你必須的
You know that you do.

104
00:09:12,990 --> 00:09:17,080
我20分鐘後準備好 很好 我給你準備點吃的
I'll be down in 20 minutes. Great. I'll make you something to eat.

105
00:09:18,470 --> 00:09:21,010
我不餓
I'm not hungry.

106
00:09:24,270 --> 00:09:26,480
昨晚怎麼了? 什麼意思?
What happened to you last night? What do you mean?

107
00:09:26,490 --> 00:09:29,240
演出結束後 你好像人間蒸發了
After the show. You just kind of disappeared.

108
00:09:29,250 --> 00:09:31,820
我不記得了
I don't remember.

109
00:09:41,990 --> 00:09:44,070
嗨 Kim副隊長 我是Jareau探員
Hi,lieutenant kim. Agent jareau.

110
00:09:44,080 --> 00:09:46,510
JJ嘛 我知道 我記得你們大部分人
Jj,of course. I remember most of you.

111
00:09:47,070 --> 00:09:50,990
Hotchner探員 Reid Morgan
Agent hotchner. Reid. Morgan.

112
00:09:51,380 --> 00:09:52,820
歡迎回到西海岸
Welcome back to the left coast.

113
00:09:52,850 --> 00:09:55,860
這兩位是Prentiss和Rossi探員 相信你沒見過他們
These are agents prentiss and rossi. I believe they're new to you.

114
00:09:56,040 --> 00:09:57,350
很高興認識你
Pleasure.

115
00:09:57,380 --> 00:10:02,040
我們已經整理出一房間 擺好玻璃板 案卷 以及超難喝的咖啡
We already have a room set up full of glass boards, case files, and extremely bad coffee.

116
00:10:02,050 --> 00:10:04,270
更艱難的我們都合作過
We've worked with a lot less.

117
00:10:04,290 --> 00:10:07,610
現在Morgan探員是老大 他說了算
Agent morgan's in charge now. It's his show.

118
00:10:08,830 --> 00:10:10,990
說來話長
Long story.

119
00:10:12,730 --> 00:10:16,060
我知道你們喜歡從最新線索入手 然後往回分析
I know you like to start with the freshest information and work your way back.

120
00:10:16,090 --> 00:10:19,650
Tara的公寓已經處理過並封鎖起來 留著讓你們去
So tara's apartment has been processed and sealed in case you want to go there.

121
00:10:19,680 --> 00:10:21,760
她的屍體 和前2個遇害的女生一起
And her body,along with that of the first 2 girls,

122
00:10:21,780 --> 00:10:24,250
都在停屍房 驗屍員隨時等候
Is at the morgue with an m.e.waiting there for your call.

123
00:10:24,260 --> 00:10:28,130
好吧 JJ 把這埵洵B妥當 和Garcia聯繫上
All right. Jj,get set up here, and then hook up with garcia.

124
00:10:28,140 --> 00:10:32,230
把目擊證人的信息傳給她 讓她同前2個遇害者的資料交叉比對
Send her the witness information so she can start crossreferencing with the first 2 victims.

125
00:10:32,240 --> 00:10:34,170
Reid 我要你閱讀所有的案卷資料
Reid,i want you to go through all the case files,

126
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:37,090
根據你對精神病理學的研究 寫一份初步側寫
Set up a preliminary profile based on what you already know about the psychopathology.

127
00:10:37,110 --> 00:10:40,200
其他人 我們去看看 從Tara身上能找到什麼
And the rest of us,let's find out what we can on tara.

128
00:11:43,100 --> 00:11:46,490
我們要找目擊證人之間的聯繫
So we're looking for a connection between the witnesses.

129
00:11:46,530 --> 00:11:49,660
吸血鬼主義者心有迷戀 他們不大會去找隨機的受害者
When vampirists become obsessed, they aren't likely to find a random victim.

130
00:11:49,680 --> 00:11:54,300
如果能找到所有受害者之間的交叉點 將能幫上大忙
If we can find a crossrelationship, someone in all the victims' lives, that'll be incredibly helpful.

131
00:11:54,600 --> 00:11:58,040
Gina King認識Tara最久 她們一起上過學
Gina king knew tara the longest. They apparently had some classes together.

132
00:11:58,050 --> 00:11:59,800
我們把她倆的關係全挖出來
Let's get all the information we can on that relationship.

133
00:11:59,830 --> 00:12:02,750
話說 把Tara所有朋友的信息都給我
As a matter of fact, get me everything you can on all of tara's friends.

134
00:12:02,760 --> 00:12:05,740
好吧 明早我會查到他們並跟蹤下去
All right. In the morning i'll track them down and do some followup.

135
00:12:05,750 --> 00:12:07,900
好的
That's fine.

136
00:12:15,050 --> 00:12:19,180
Dante 這位是<金屬人生>的Jeff
Dante. This is jeff from "metal life" magazine.

137
00:12:19,190 --> 00:12:21,500
他在寫一篇關於藝術家跨界風格...
He's writing a story on artists who cross over…

138
00:12:21,510 --> 00:12:26,370
"跨界" 我還有"跨界風格"呀 <金屬人生>的Jeff?
Cross over. Is that what I do,jeff from "metal life"?

139
00:12:26,830 --> 00:12:29,270
算是呀 你的音樂也不是 純粹的哥特 對吧?
I guess,kind of. You're not totally goth,right?

140
00:12:29,280 --> 00:12:31,190
吸血鬼的這檔子事兒...
That whole vampire thing you do is…

141
00:12:31,220 --> 00:12:33,650
啊 吸血鬼的這檔子事兒?
Ah,the vampire thing?

142
00:12:33,660 --> 00:12:38,050
對 你的表演 對特定的人群很有吸引力
Yeah,your act. It appeals to certain people.

143
00:12:38,060 --> 00:12:43,540
絕望又痛苦的人們 盡力又無力掌控現實 我的音樂對他們最有吸引力
It appeals to desperate, sad people with,at best,a tenuous hold on reality.

144
00:12:46,350 --> 00:12:48,290
我能引用你這句話嗎?
Can I quote you on that?

145
00:12:48,820 --> 00:12:51,130
可以 請自便吧
Sure. Knock yourself out.

146
00:12:52,760 --> 00:12:56,710
別 可別引用那句話 我能把他拉回來 再...
No,don't use that quote. 'Cause I can just get him back, get another…

